The paper deals with optimal decoding of bit interleaved coded modulation (BICM) MIMO-OFDM systems under imperfect channel estimation. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), communication systems (cs.COMM), systems and control (cs.SY), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and multimedia (cs.MM). Given the focus on channel estimation and decoding, cs.IT and cs.COMM are the most likely sub-categories. The use of Bayesian methods and outage rates suggests cs.SY as a possible sub-category. The use of MIMO-OFDM systems suggests cs.NI as a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of coded modulation suggests cs.MM as a possible sub-category.
